<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910930-0028</DOCNO><DOCID>910930-0028.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Ferruzzi Finanziaria S.p.A.:   Concern's Profit Fell 54%   To $58 Million in 1st Half</HL><DATE>09/30/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8</SO><CO>   I.FFI MNT</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)CONGLOMERATES (CGL)</MS><IN>CONGLOMERATES (CGL)CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)RESTRUCTURINGS, RECAPITALIZATION (RCN)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)ITALY (ITA)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Italy's Ferruzzi Finanziaria S.p.A. said consolidatedprofit plunged 54% to 83 billion lire ($58 million) in thefirst half from 180 billion lire a year earlier.   Revenue rose to 8.631 trillion lire from 8.352 trillionlire.</LP><TEXT>   Ferruzzi is the central holding company of the Italianindustrial Ferruzzi-Montedison group.   The company said, noting the continuing restructure sincethe merger of its units Montedison S.p.A. and FerruzziAgricola Finanziari S.p.A., that results for the year areexpected to be modestly positive.</TEXT></DOC>